<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=36></a><b><br>Wizard Protest on Innoruuk</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 17:12 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>From Argos:<br><br>A wizard protest is being held today to discuss topics such as the spell resistance cap. All supporters are welcome.<br><br>Server: Prexus<br>Zone: West Freeport<br>Day: Friday Sept. 24<br>Time: 6:00pm pst, 9:00pm est<br><br>Thanks! <br></font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=37></a><b><br>Test Server News</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 17:08 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>The following changes have been implemented with the latest patch, most importantly, changes to corpse resurrection. It should be noted that all corpses generated previous to this patch may not be resurrected, however, all corpses generated from this point forward may be resurrected with the changes listed below applying.<br><br><ul><li> Corpses that are older than 2 hours cannot be resurrected.<br>  <li> Corpses that are produced from a duel cannot be resurrected after 10 minutes.<br></ul><br><br>General Enhancements<br><br><ul><li> A Yes/No request window is now brought up when ever turning in the PK note to the Priest of Discord.<br>  <li> It is now possible to manually reorganize icons within the spell book.<br>  <li> Pet damage inflicted during PvP combat has been slightly reduced. <br>  <li> It is now possible to place items marked as &quot;No Drop&quot; in the bank.<br></ul><br><br>The EverQuest Team<br></font></td></tr>
</table></td></tr></table>
<table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td BGCOLOR=#800000><b><font face="Comic Sans MS" color=#FFFF00 size=2>&nbsp;18 September 1999, Saturday</font></b></td></tr>
<tr><td><table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=5 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100%>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=38></a><b><br>GM Event on Mithaniel Marr</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 07:16 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>From Theosis Korondor:<br><br>GM Event on Mithaniel Marr Server:<br><br>The Unrest in Unrest (told in third person)<br>A stalwart band of adventurers of the guild Vanguard of Marr were headed to Unrest for the night. It was this place they had learned they could obtain Bloodstained Tunics for the many rangers in their guild. During the trip through Dagnors Cauldron, they heard a few rumors about some adventurers of the evil races running about slaying those trying to rid Faydwer of the undead that infest the place. Vanguard of Marr charged on to face the evil beings, and hopefully clear a path for all others to continue the assault on the Estate of Unrest Castle.<br><br>Upon stepping onto the property, Wizard Theosis was greeted by a shrunken female Ogre wearing plate mail and toting a nasty looking 2 handed sword with a blackened appearance to it. Being a follower of Quellios the Peaceful, he attempted to communicate with the Ogre. Taking offense to his wave, she began beating the life-force out of Theosis' frail body. Shaman Aaross and Cleric Venyent tried healing Theosis faster than this nasty ogre could take his life-force, but their efforts were in vain. Theosis was forced to flee. This ogre, who remains nameless in my mind, then commenced to take delayed offense to the healers saving the life of the one who offended her by waving! Aaross was forced to flee, but Venyent was spared her wrath when many others began to swarm about to aid us in our battle.<br><br>Shortly after, Vanguard of Marr regrouped with Wizard Gerard and Druid Arduinna and discovered that this Ogre was the leader of 2 or three more nasty critters. After a battle that seemed to take hours, Guild master Ranger Kel’anth Ra’Dar landed the killing blow on the wretched beast that assaulted his favorite Erudite Wizard. Kel’anth was heavily wounded, but the prize seemed well worth their troubles. Kel’anth searched the ogre’s body and found a Rubicite Breastplate and a Black Iron Bastard Sword!<br><br>It simply must have been Mithaniel Marr himself granting a reward to those that risked their lives in the name of all that is good in Norrath!<br><br>Thanks! <br></font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=39></a><b><br>LA Player Gathering</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 07:13 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>From Wes Parker:<br><br>On Saturday, October 2, a large group of players of the massivelymultiplayer online game EverQuest will be meeting at Veteran's Memorial Park in Culver City. For most of the attendees, it will be the first time meeting people with whom they have interacted exclusively from within an online world. The game is set in the sword and sorcery genre has developed its own subculture. It has been described as the &quot;digitalversion of crack&quot; (Hunter Godfrey, quoted in Wired Online), as manyplayers spend as much of their free time as possible playing the game. Since the adventure of the game is completely dependent upon the interaction between the players, EverQuest has put to rest the commonly held assumption that computer gaming is a solitary activity. So what will happen when these online aficionados get together in flesh and blood for a day of merriment in the real world? We will soon find out.<br><br>The event began as a casual post by player Kevin Scott on an Internet site devoted to the game, inviting fellow players in the Los Angeles area to &quot;come hang out at a park or something&quot;. Over the course of the following few days, the scope of the event grew to include over 150 attendees. Some attendees will be coming from as far as Florida to attend the event. The get together has also drawn the attention of several representatives of Verant Interactive, one of the threecompanies responsible for bringing EverQuest to life. These membersinclude the Verant CEO, John Smedley, and several members of the game's development team, who will be attending the event.<br><br>To keep up to date on the developing plans for this event, please visit:<br><a href=http://www.csunbooks.com/eq> <a href=http://www.csunbooks.com/eq>http://www.csunbooks.com/eq</a></a><br><br>Also, an update from the LA Event site:<br><br>09/15/99 <br>Just when I thought the registration rate was slowing down, we got 32 more registrants, raising our expected turnout to this event to 183! Thanks for all the interest everyone, and keep publicizing this on your severs and on the message boards. <br><br>There is an issue with the park in that we need a permit to bring this many people to the park, and Veteran’s Memorial Park isn’t going to be available for us on that day. I’m leaving in a few hours for a weekend trip to New Zealand (I’m the best man in a wedding), but the coordination team is working on this issue. More information as it becomes available. <br><br>As of now, the date still stands, but we have to decide on a different venue, which we will select from the list of alternates that we have.<br><br>Thanks! <br></font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=40></a><b><br>Crafting Raw Silk Armor</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 07:05 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>From Elos:<br><br>Around 8:00 pm est I was told by a Cleric named Archurian how to make raw-silk armor. This is the first person I have heard of to make the armor so I give credit to him =). Here is how to do it. You will need a large sewing kit and a skill lvl of 20 (hehe this is real easy stuff to make) and some spider silk. First you take spider silk (not spiderling silk you need to get this silk from there full grown brothers). Now you take 2 spider silks and put it in your large sewing kit. Hit combine you will get a silk swatch (this was trivial to me at skill lvl 25) now that you have the silk swatch you take that and put it the large sewing kit with the pattern of your choice. Hit combine and whalla. You get a raw-silk item =) easy right? Tunic/Robes and pants take 2 swatches to make all others take 1. The items can be worn by the pure magic classes and monks. due to there low wt. they are good for both groups. They have one ac over cloth so they are really only good for low to mid lvl. The robe that you make looks like a light brown (like the thurm robe). None of the garments have any magic stats on them. I have been charging about a plat for each garment and 2pp for robe and pants.. I have been selling everything I make to hehe. Due to the low lvl of skill needed to make the armor I don't think you can charge much more then that. I would encourage each of you to tell as many people as you can on how to make silk. I think that if we have a free flow of information we will quickly be able to figure out what Verant made with this patch =). <br>P.S. Spider silk can be found on giant spiders which inhabit many zones throughout norrath. <br><br>Also, from Halelil of Bristlebane:<br><br>Many people who have found out about making raw-silk armor do not wish to reveal the information to the majority, but I feel everyone has a right to know. So far I have learned that you need to make swatches to make raw-silk armor. To make a swatch you combine 2 Spider silks(not spiderling) in a lg or sm sewing kit. You then put in a pattern with the swatch and combine to make a piece of raw-silk armor. To make a tunic and leggings, you need to stack 2 swatches and the pattern. Enjoy, I usually sell these items for 5gp each, for the cost of the spider silk, 3gp, and pattern, 6sp. If you have any questions <a href=mailto:Thomas874@aol.com> e-mail me</a>, I will gladly answer any questions. <br><br>Thanks! <br></font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=41></a><b><br>Bertox xTailoring Quests</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 06:59 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>From the Mynn &amp; Savin Tailoring Emporium of Bertox:<br><br>The Mynn &amp; Savin Tailoring emporium is focused on delivering the finest tailored clothes in all of Bertox. Recent breakthroughs have been made in tailoring after many grueling hours and weeks of research.<br>The collective talents of the Emporium have discovered how to make Raw Silk Clothes, but there is more and the secrets are hidden in New Tailoring Books found on NPCs as loot. We don't where or who. But we know there is more.<br><br>We know there is a whip pattern.<br><br>There is still no knowledge of how to use the mystical Quiver and Fleeting Quiver Patterns. <br><br>There are rumors of pure silk, and even magical silk robes.<br><br>The first person to bring us each new book will get 35plat. That’s 35plat for each new book found.<br><br>Help the Tailors, find the missing secrets, get better clothing for you friends and family.<br><br>If you find one of these Fine Books please contact Mynn, Savin or Ancrominia. If these are not available, contact any Jester who will help point you in the right direction.<br><br>This Quest is Sponsored by Mynn &amp; Savin Tailoring Emporium of Bertox.<br><br>This quest is open to both Jesters Club Members and non-Jesters.<br><br>For more information and updates and progress on Jesters Events and Quests please visit <a href=http://www.jestersclub.com> <a href=http://www.jestersclub.com>http://www.jestersclub.com</a> </a><br><br>Also:<br>The Mynn and Savin Tailoring Emporium is happy to announce the Fall Clothing Special.<br>The masses of Norrath are facing ever increasing pressure from the evil around us. We need to equip of younger adventures with better, lighter armor. We need cat skins to do this, and only the best will do for these brave adventures. But most of all we need your assistance in the Quest.<br><br>We will pay 4gp for each HQ Cat Skin delivered to us,(see details below). There are also prizes for the characters that deliver the most during the month. Depending on Charisma you can buy these skins from vendors for 1-2gp. You can kill defenseless animals as well if that is your wish. We don't care how you got them. As long as it was done honestly. The location of the deliveries:<br><br><ul><li> Look For Mynn or Ancromina -- Master Jesters. <br>  <li> Each Thursday and Tuesday Evenings. <br>  <li> 8pm EDT-9pm EDT High Keep (bank).<br>  <li> 9pm EDT till 10pm EDT North Freeport (bank).<br></ul><br><br>If any evil races need pickups Ancrominia will head out to the East Commonlands about 10:15 EDT and hang out in the tunnel for half an hour or so.<br>We only guarantee to honor this quest for the first 500 delivered between now and October 15th. We will announce when we hit 500 and will update this event board with the delivered total to date. And at the end we will publish the results and announce the winners.<br><br>In addition, there will be some special prizes for the character that brings in the most pelts. First prize will be a set of reinforced armor, valued at over 80plat. Other prizes of armor will also be handed out to runners up. Including full suits of Raw Silk Armor for Monks and Mage Types.<br><br>Thanks! <br></font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=42></a><b><br>Additional Guild Commands Petition...</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 06:54 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>From Anduril Valar the Tareldar Paladin:<br><br>Well, the Additional Guild Commands Petition has been on the EQ Haven website for two and a half days now and we have already received over 250 signatures! I have written a letter to Mr. McQuaid and Mr. Butler concerning this petition but no word back from them yet (of course, I only set it just yesterday so hopefully on Monday we may get some feedback). I just want to thank everyone who has signed it and I hope these simple but very useful commands do become part of the world we know as Everquest soon. For those of you who have not heard about the petition (and how could you have not, I think I had it in the news on Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesay!), let me give you a brief description on it. This petition would add the following commands:<br><br>/guildwhoall - This command will list ALL members of the guild, whether they are ingame or not. A FANTASTIC tool for guildmasters and officers and just for members who want to know who is in their guild.<br><br>/guildwho - This command will list all members of the guild that are currently online. Great to know who is on in your guild.<br><br>/rank - To be able to supply your own rank (Only officers or the GM could do this).<br><br>Furthermore, I would like to reiterate that the /guildwhoall and /guildwho functions are NOT /who functions, they are /guild functions. With that said, only members IN that particular guild could use them, just like /guildsay.<br><br>So, if you have not yet voted but would like to or would like more information on this, follow this link to EQ Haven and let your voice be heard!<br><br><a href=http://www.eqhaven.com/petition_guilds.shtml<br><br>> <a href=http://www.eqhaven.com/petition_guilds.shtml>http://www.eqhaven.com/petition_guilds.shtml</a><br><br></a></font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2><font color=#800000><a name=43></a><b><br>Xegony Rescue Quest</b></font><font color=#006600 size=1> [ <a href=mailto:eq_trade@usa.net target=main><font color=#006600>ShadowMaster</font></a> at 06:53 CST ]</font></font></tr></td>
<tr><td><font face="Comic Sans MS" size=2>From Leber:<br><br>Good citizens of Xegony - I need your help!<br>For many years I have slaved away to the every whims of the foulsouls known as Darkmoon, an evil group of dark elves that haveterrorized the honest citizens of Norrath. I have done this against mywill only to keep my children alive while they sit among filth,imprisoned in the dark elf city of Neriak. The High Lord Graffe ofDarkmoon is holding my children captive just inside the walls of thecity but try as I might; I have not been able to free them. The lastresort to free my children was to raid the Darkmoon treasury and stealone of their most prized artifacts, a staff of some power, and hold itfor exchange in the release of my young ones. <br><br>A note from my son Jallaan was smuggled out of Neriak and hasreached my hands; alas my hopes to free them have been dashed. Itappears that the evil races are gathering soon to hunt me down and killme. I wish not to have my head used as some heathen's doorstop, so Ihave gone into hiding with no hope of getting my children back. I call out now to my friends and good citizens of Norrath to aid mein my time of need. My children sit now just inside the gates of thedark elf city waiting to be released from captivity. If any of Norrath'sgood people were to gather together and free Jallaan and Gwena fromcaptivity, I would be able to come out of hiding and leave my terms ofslavery. In turn for this great deed, I'm willing to turn over all theartifacts that I have pilfered from the Darkmoon treasury to those whorescue my young ones and deliver them back to Halas safe.<br><br>I have seen the guards of Neriak and know this will be no easy taskto accomplish. The first group that is able to enter the city anddeliver the two children back to Halas will have all the hoardedtreasure in my bank within Halas.<br><br>Please aid me in my time of need, you will not regret the help youlend me.All those interested in freeing my children should meet at the entranceto Nektulos on the East Commonland side, Sunday, September 19th at 9 amPST (12 noon EST). <br><br>Thank you my friends, <br><br>Leber of the Xegony Frozen North <br><br>( ooc/ This quest is open for &quot;light&quot; races only. The two barbarianswill be waiting just inside the Neriak Foreign Quarter zone and willgroup with the first adventurers that zone through. The group will needto make their way out of Nektulos before any spell or song can be usedupon the two barbarian captives (example: invisibility, teleport,cloud...), but the two barbarians will aid in the escape anyway they can(including SoW if needed). In the event that one of the barbies diesalong the way, they will need to be escorted back to their body fromFreeport zone. Once the group reaches Halas, Jallaan will retrieve apack from the bank and turn it over to the leader of the group. The pack will include many magic items and a rare, high quality bear hide, total value is close to 1000 plat.)<br><br>Thanks! <br></font></td></tr>
